# Supabase Migration Plan

## Goal
Migrate the Pharmacy Audit backend database from local SQLite to cloud-hosted Supabase (PostgreSQL) so the application can be accessed from anywhere via a browser.

## Credentials
- Supabase credentials are stored in `server/.env` (not committed to git)

## Strategy
Use `@supabase/supabase-js` (the official Supabase JS client) instead of the `pg` library, as it works natively with our secret key. All complex SQL queries will be migrated to use Supabase's JavaScript query builder.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] server/package.json
- Remove: `sqlite3`, `better-sqlite3`
- Add: `@supabase/supabase-js`, `dotenv`

#### [NEW] server/.env
- `SUPABASE_URL=<your-project-url>`
- `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=<your-secret-key>`

#### [MODIFY] server/db.js
- Remove all SQLite code
- Create and export Supabase client using env vars

#### [MODIFY] server/server.js
- Replace all `run()`, `get()`, `all()` SQLite calls with Supabase client queries
- Keep all API routes and business logic identical

#### [MODIFY] server/import.js
- Replace SQLite batch inserts with Supabase batch upserts

#### [MODIFY] server/export.js
- Replace SQLite queries with Supabase queries

### SQL Schema (run in Supabase SQL Editor)
- Create all 5 tables in PostgreSQL syntax
- Seed default users

## Verification Plan
1. Restart server and check it connects to Supabase without error
2. Create an audit session via the API
3. Import an Excel file and verify rows appear in Supabase dashboard
4. Test auditor count updates reflect in real time
